CID officers have been deployed at the NCPB to monitor distribution of subsidised fertiliser to stop cartels from diverting it.The government is distributing 104,000 tonnes of fertiliser to farmers for the current planting season. Agriculture CS Willy Bett said staff at the NCPB found colluding with cartels to divert the fertiliser will be arrested and prosecuted.He says the fertiliser will be easily accessed by farmers at all NCPB depots. However, the farmers expressed fear that cartels are still taking advantage of the distribution system at the NCPB.The government has been registering all farmers and the acreage of land they own as a condition for getting the fertiliser.Some cartels are said to have registered as farmers with huge tracts of non-existent land to get the subsidisedfertiliser.